#
#  clipanion distinctive features:
#    - TYPESCRIPT-FIRST + CLASS-BASED — each subcommand is a class
#      extending `Command`; option fields use `Option.X(...)` field
#      decorators (similar to Python click decorators but as class
#      fields)
#    - `static paths = [['path'], ['alias'], Command.Default]` —
#      MULTI-PATH ARRAY where each inner array is a path segment;
#      supports NESTED PATHS like `[['workspace', 'build'], ['ws',
#      'b']]` for `mytool workspace build` and aliases
#    - `Command.Default` — special sentinel making this command the
#      DEFAULT when no path matches (no-args case)
#    - `static usage = Command.Usage({ description, details,
#      examples })` — metadata for auto-help generation
#    - `Option.String('-s,--long', { description, env, required,
#      validator })` — STRING option field
#    - `Option.Boolean('-f,--flag', { description })` — BOOLEAN flag
#    - `Option.Array('--items', { description })` — REPEATABLE array
#    - `Option.Counter('-v', { description })` — COUNTER (`-vvv` = 3)
#    - `Option.Rest({ name })` — REST POSITIONAL (collects all
#      remaining)
#    - `Option.Proxy({ name })` — PROXY all subsequent args verbatim
#      (passes through to underlying command)
#    - `Option.String({ required: true })` — REQUIRED option
#      (errors if missing)
#    - `Option.String({ env: 'ENV_NAME' })` — ENV VAR FALLBACK
#    - `Option.String({ validator: t.isEnum([...]) })` — TYPED
#      VALIDATOR from typanion package (Maël Nison's companion
#      validation library)
#    - `Option.String({ validator: t.isNumber() })` — number validator
#    - `async execute(): Promise<number | void>` — ASYNC COMMAND
#      BODY; return value becomes exit code (default 0)
#    - `this.context` — CONTEXT object with stdout/stderr/stdin
#      (caller-provided, allows DI for testing)
#    - `this.cli` — CLI instance reference
#    - `this.help` — boolean indicating --help was requested
#    - `cli.register(CommandClass)` — REGISTER subcommand class
#    - `cli.runExit(argv)` — RUN and call process.exit with command's
#      return value
#    - `cli.run(argv, context?)` — RUN without exit (returns Promise
#      of exit code)
#    - `cli.process(argv)` — PARSE and return Command instance without
#      running execute() (for testing)
#    - `Builtins.HelpCommand` — auto-injected `--help` command
#    - `Builtins.VersionCommand` — auto-injected `--version` command
#    - `Builtins.TokensCommand` — debug command showing parsed tokens
#    - `Builtins.DefinitionsCommand` — show command definitions in JSON
#    - DEFINITELY-TYPED — full TypeScript type definitions; option
#      values are TYPED based on field declaration (e.g. `Option.
#      Boolean` field is typed as `boolean`)
#    - TREE-SHAKEABLE — caller only imports what they use
#    - LAZY-LOADED COMMANDS via cli.register(class) — class registration
#      is sync, but execute() can lazy-import deps
#  Distinct from R340 TypeScript-Node oclif (Salesforce's CLI
#  framework with plugin system + decorators-based class commands —
#  closest concept analog but heavier with plugin/topic infrastructure
#  and more opinionated about command discovery), R341 TypeScript-
#  Node yargs (Node.js fluent builder via `.option('name', {})` /
#  `.command('cmd', desc, builder, handler)` chains — function-based
#  vs class-based), R343 TypeScript-Node tj/commander.js (Node.js
#  fluent builder by TJ Holowaychuk — fluent builder vs class-based),
#  R393 TypeScript-Node meow (Sindre Sorhus's CLI helper — usage-
#  string + flags schema, single command only), R395 node:util.parse
#  Args (Node stdlib — much lower-level), R396 TypeScript-Node sade
#  (Luke Edwards's tiny commander alt — function-based), R400
#  TypeScript-Node cac (EGOIST's tiny commander alt — function-based),
#  R402 TypeScript-Node minimist (substack's original — single
#  function call).  clipanion's approach: TYPESCRIPT-FIRST + CLASS-
#  BASED design with `class X extends Command` + `static paths`
#  multi-path arrays + `static usage` metadata + `Option.X(...)`
#  typed option fields (String/Boolean/Array/Counter/Rest/Proxy) +
#  `async execute()` async command body + `this.context` DI-friendly
#  context + Builtins.HelpCommand/VersionCommand/TokensCommand/
#  DefinitionsCommand + typanion validator integration + tree-
#  shakeable + lazy-loaded commands — corpus's **first documented
#  TypeScript-first-class-based-with-typed-option-fields Node.js CLI
#  library**.  Brings cross-language CLI library taxonomy variant
#  count to 142; TypeScript-Node ecosystem now has 9 documented CLI
#  libraries — TIED FOR FIRST-MOST-DOCUMENTED CLI LANGUAGE alongside
#  Rust (9) and Go (9) at the TOP TIER of the cross-language CLI
#  library taxonomy.
#
#  Surface (verbatim from `cli/src/cli.ts` + `cli/src/commands/{Init,
#  Generate}Command.ts`):
#
#  Subcommands:
#
#    init                           Initialize a new OpenAPI codegen
#                                   config file (interactive prompt)
#    -c, --config FILE              Configuration file path
#        --dry-run                  Print the file to stdout
#
#    generate [NAMESPACE] (alias: gen, default)
#                                   Generate types & components from
#                                   an OpenAPI file
#    -c, --config FILE              Configuration file path
#                                   (env OPENAPI_CODEGEN_CONFIG)
#        --source TYPE              Source: file | url | github
#                                   (env OPENAPI_CODEGEN_SOURCE)
#
#    [source=file] options:
#        --relativePath PATH        Relative path of spec file
#                                   (env OPENAPI_CODEGEN_FILE_PATH)
#
#    [source=url] options:
#        --url URL                  URL of spec file
#                                   (env OPENAPI_CODEGEN_URL)
#        --method METHOD            HTTP method: get | post
#                                   (env OPENAPI_CODEGEN_URL_METHOD)
#
#    [source=github] options:
#        --owner OWNER              Repository owner
#                                   (env OPENAPI_CODEGEN_GITHUB_OWNER)
#        --repository, --repo REPO  Repository name
#                                   (env OPENAPI_CODEGEN_GITHUB_REPOSITORY)
#        --ref REF                  Git ref (commit sha, branch, tag)
#                                   (env OPENAPI_CODEGEN_GITHUB_REF)
#        --specPath PATH            OpenAPI spec file path
#                                   (env OPENAPI_CODEGEN_GITHUB_SPEC_PATH)
#        --pr, --pull-request NUM   Select a pull-request as ref
#                                   (env OPENAPI_CODEGEN_GITHUB_PULL_REQUEST)
#
#  Auto-injected by clipanion Builtins:
#    -h, --help                     Show help
#        --version                  Show version
#
#  Dup-skipped neighbors during hunt (in corpus or also clipanion
#  users):
#    - yarn (IN CORPUS via _yarn — Yarn package manager Berry 2+;
#      uses clipanion as its CLI framework; flagship clipanion use
#      case — clipanion was created BY Maël Nison FOR Yarn Berry)
#    - pnpm (IN CORPUS via _pnpm — uses Yarn-derived plugins via
#      @yarnpkg/cli which is built on clipanion)
#    - allure (IN CORPUS via _allure — but that's Allure 2, the
